<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 04 at 9:27AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Reduced Visibility this Morning due to Fog...
Fog, locally dense near the Helena and West Yellowstone Areas,
is on-going this morning within some valleys of Southwest and
Central Montana. Motorist should be prepared for reduced
visibility to generally 1 to 3 miles; however, as low as a quarter
mile near the cities Helena and West Yellowstone. Slow down and
use your low beam headlights when driving through fog. The fog is
expected to dissipate between 10 and 11 this morning.</description>
